page.title: 05Ecology-Capel Nature Reserve
page.content: The Capel Countryside Club,open to anybody,looks after the council owned reserve. in our survey of the reserve we found water insects and leeches in the stream under the bridge.Further into the reserve there are birds such as yellow and grey wagtails,cuckoos and house martins.An owl lives in a black Italian poplar tree.The most common trees are Oak,Poplar and Ash.Animals in the reserve are foxes,voles,mice and shrews.There could be badgers. There is some pollution.There are lots of pieces of glass in the stream.Worst of all there is clay with bits of oil in it.
